obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37109)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 2, for section 1.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37109&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[1. Short title, extent and application.--(1) This Act may be called the Official Secrets Act, 1923.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India and applies also to servants of the Government and to citizens of`
  line `India outside India].`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37110)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37110&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,`
  line
  line `(1) any reference to a place belonging to Government includes a place occupied by any`
  line `department of the Government, whether the place is or is not actually vested in Government;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) expressions referring to commnicating or receiving include any communicating or receiving,`
  line `whether in whole or in part, and whether the sketch, plan, model, article, note, document, or`
  line `information itself or the substance, effect or description thereof only be communicated or received;`
  line `expressions referring to obtaining or retaining any sketch, plan, model, article, note or document,`
  line `include the copying or causing to be copied of the whole or any part of any sketch, plan, model,`
  line `article, note, or document; and expressions referring to the communication of any sketch, plan, model,`
  line `article, note or document include the transfer or transmission of the sketch, plan, model, article, note`
  line `or document;`
  line
  line `(3) "document' includes part of a document;`
  line
  line `(4) "model" includes design, pattern and specimen;`
  line
  line `(5) "munitions of war" includes the whole or any part of any ship, submarine, aircraft, tank or`
  line `similar engine, arms and ammunition, torpedo, or mine intended or adapted for use in war, and any`
  line `other article, material, or device, whether actual or proposed, intended for such use;`
  line
  line `(6) "office under Government" inlcudes any office or employment is or under any department of the`
  line `Government ^2`
  line ***;
  line
  line `(7) "photograph" includes an undeveloped film or plate;`
  line
  line `(8)"prohibited place" means`
  line
  line `(a) any work of defence, arsenal, naval, military or air force establishment or station,`
  line `mine, minefield, camp, ship or aircraft belonging to, or occupied by or on behalf of,`
  line `Government, any military telegraph or telephone so belonging or occupied, any wireless or`
  line `signal station or office so belonging or occupied and any factory, dockyard or other place so`
  line `belonging or occupied and used for the purpose of building, repairing, making or storing any`
  line `munitions of war, or any sketches, plans, models or documents relating thereto, or for the`
  line `purpose of getting any metals, oil or minerals of use in time of war;`
  line
  line `(b) any place not belonging to Government where any munitions of war or any sketches,`
  line `models, plans or documents relating thereto, are being made, repaired, gotten or stores`
  line `under contract with, or with any person on behalf of, Government, or otherwise on behalf`
  line `of Government;`
  line
  line `(c) any place belonging to or used for the purpose of Government which is for the time`
  line `being declared by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, to be a`
  line `prohibited place for the purposes of this Act on the ground that information with respect`
  line `thereto, or damage thereto, would be useful to an enemy, and to which a copy of the`
  line `notification in respect thereof has been affixed in English 'and in the vernacular of the`
  line locality;
  line
  line `(d) any railway, road, way or channel, or other means of communication by land or water`
  line `(including any works or structures being part thereof or connected therewith) or any place`
  line `used for gas, water or electricity works or other works for purposes of a public character, or`
  line `any place where any munitions of war or any sketches, models, plans, or documents relating`
  line `thereto, arc being made, repaired, or stored otherwise than on behalf of Government, which is`
  line `for the time being declared by the Central Government, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, to be a prohibited place for the purposes of this Act on the ground that information`
  line `with respect thereto, or the destruction of obstruction thereof, or interference therewith,`
  line `would beuseful to an enemy, and to which a copy of the notification in respect thereof has`
  line `been affixed in English and in the vernacular of the locality;`
  line
  line `(9) "sketch" includes any photograph or other mode of representing any place or thing; and`
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(10) "Superintendent of Police" includes any police officer of a like or superior rank, and`
  line `any person upon whom the powers of a Superintendent of Police are for the purposes of this`
  line `Act conferred by the Central Government.`
  line ^4
  line ***
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (1A) ins. by the A.O. 1937, omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line `2. The words or of the Government of the United Kingdom or of any British Possession omitted by Act 24 of 1967, s. 3.`
  line `3. Clause (9A) ins. by the A.O. 1950 and omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line `4. The words "or by any Local Government" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37111)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Penalties for spying.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37111&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person for any purpose prejudicial to the safety or`
  line `interests of the State--`
  line
  line `(a) approaches, inspects, passes over or is in the vicinity of, or enters, any prohibited`
  line `place; or`
  line
  line `(b) makes any sketch, plan, model, ornote which is calculated to be or might be or`
  line `is intended to be, directly or indirectly, useful to an enemy; or`
  line
  line `(c) obtains, collects, records or publishes or communicates to any other person any secret official`
  line `code or pass word, or any sketch, plan, model, article or note or other document or information which`
  line `is calculated to be or might be or is intended to be, directly or indirectly, useful to an enemy ^1[or`
  line `which relates to a matter the disclosure of which is likely to affect the sovereignty and integrity of`
  line `India, the security of the State or friendly relations with foreign States];`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend, where the offence is committed`
  line `in relation to any work of defence, arsenal, naval, military or air force establishment or station, mine,`
  line `minefield, factory, dockyard, camp, ship or aircraft or otherwise in relation to the naval, military or air`
  line `force affairs of Government or in relation to any secret official code, to fourteen years and in other cases`
  line `to three years.`
  line
  line `(2) On a prosecution for an offence punishable under this section ^2***, it shall not be necessary to`
  line `show that the accused person was guilty of any particular act tending to show a purpose prejudicial to the`
  line `safety or interests of the State, and, notwithstanding that no such act is proved against him, he may be`
  line `convicted if, from the circumstances of the case or his conduct or his known character as proved, it`
  line `appears that his purpose was a purpose prejudicial to the safety or interests of the State; and if any sketch,`
  line `plan, model, article, note, document, or information relating to or used in any prohibited place, or relating`
  line `to any thing in such a place, or any secret official code or pass word is made, obtained, collected,`
  line `recorded, published or communicated by any person other than a person acting under lawful authority,`
  line `and from the circumstances of the case or his conduct or his known character as proved it appears that his`
  line `purpose was a purpose prejudicial to the safety or interests of the State, such sketch, plan, model, article,`
  line `note, document, ^3[information, code or pass word shall be presumed to have been made], obtained,`
  line `collected, recorded, published or communicated for a purpose prejudicial to the safety or interests of the`
  line State.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. The words with imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years omitted by s. 4, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "or information shall be presumed to have been made".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37112)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Communications with foreign agents to be evidence of commission of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37112&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) In`
  line `any proceedings against a person for an offence under section 3, the fact that he has been in`
  line `communication with, or attempted to communicate with a foreign agent, whether within or without`
  line `^1[India], shall be relevant for the purpose of proving that he has, for a purpose prejudicial to the safety or`
  line `interests of the State, obtained-or attempted to obtain information which is calculated to be or might be, or`
  line `is intended to be, directly or indirectly, useful to any enemy.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of this section, but without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing`
  line provision,
  line
  line `(a) a person may be presumed to have been in communication with a foreign agent if--`
  line
  line `(i) he has, either within or without ^1[India]; visited the address of a foreign agent or consorted`
  line `or associated with a foreign agent, or`
  line
  line `(ii) either within or without ^1India], the name or address of, or any other information`
  line `regarding, a foreign agent has been found in his possession, or has been obtained by him from`
  line `any other person;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "foreign agent" includes any person who is or has been or in respect of whom`
  line `it appears that there are reasonable grounds for suspecting him of being or having been employed by a`
  line `foreign power, either directly or indirectly, for the purpose of committing an act, either within or`
  line `without ^1[India], prejudicial to the safety or interests of the State, or who has or is reasonably`
  line `suspected of having, either within or without ^1[India], committed, Or attempted to commit, such an`
  line `act in the interests of a foreign power;`
  line
  line `(c) any address, whether within or without ^1[India], in respect of which it appears that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for suspecting it of being an address used for the receipt of communications`
  line `intended for a foreign agent, or any address at which a foreign agent resides, or to which he resorts for`
  line `the purpose of giving or receiving communications, or at which he carries on any business, may be`
  line `presumed to be the address of a foreign agent, and communications addressed to such an address to`
  line `be communications with a foreign agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37113)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Wrongful communication, etc., of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37113&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person having in his possession`
  line `or control any secret official code or pass word or any sketch, plan, model, article, note, document or`
  line `information which relates to or is used in a prohibited place or relates to anything in such a place, ^1`
  line [or
  line `which is likely to assist, directly or indirectly, an enemy or which relates to a matter the disclosure of`
  line `which is likely to affect the sovereignty and integrity of India, the security of the State or friendly`
  line `relations with foreign States or which has been made or obtained in contravention of this Act,] or`
  line `which has been entrusted in confidence to him by any person holding office under Government, or which`
  line `he has obtained or to which he has had access owing to his position as a person who holds or has held`
  line `office under Government, or as a person who holds or has held a contract made, on behalf of`
  line `Government, or as a person who is or has been employed under a person who holds or has held`
  line `such an office or contract—`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully communicates the code or pass word, sketch, plan, model, article, note, document or`
  line `information to any person other than a person to whom he is authorised to communicate it or a Court`
  line `of Justice or a person to whom it is, in the interests of the State his duty to communicate it; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses the information in his possession for the benefit of any foreign power or in any other`
  line `manner prejudicial to the safety of the State; or`
  line
  line `(c) retains the sketch, plan, model, article, note or document in his possession or control`
  line `when he has no right to retain it, or when it is contrary to his duty to retain it, or wilfully fails to`
  line `comply with all directions issued by lawful authority with regard to the return or disposal`
  line `thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to take reasonable care of, or so conducts himself as to endanger the safety of,`
  line `the sketch, plan, model, article, note, document, secret official code or pass word or`
  line information;
  line
  line `he shall be guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person voluntarily receives any secret official code or pass word or any sketch, plan, model,`
  line `article, note, document or information knowing or having reasonable ground to believe, at the time when`
  line `he receives it, that the code, pass word, sketch, plan, model, article, note, document or information is`
  line `communicated in contravention of this Act, he shall be guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person having in his possession or control any sketch, plan, model, article, note,`
  line `document or information, which relates to munitions of war, communicates it, directly or indirectly, to any foreign power or in any other manner prejudicial to the safety or interests of the State, he`
  line `shall be guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(4) A person guilty of an offence under this section shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 5, for "or which has been made or obtained in contravention of this Act,".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 5, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f.10-7-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37114)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Unauthorised use of uniforms; falsification of reports, forgery, personation, and falsedocuments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37114&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person for the purpose of gaining admission or of assisting any other`
  line `person to gain admission to a prohibited place or for any other purpose prejudicial to the safety of`
  line `the State--`
  line
  line `(a) uses or wears, without lawful authority, any naval, military, air force, police or other official`
  line `uniform, or any uniform so nearly, resembling the same as to be calculated to deceive, or falsely`
  line `represents himself to be a person who is or has been entitled to use or wear any such uniform; or`
  line
  line `(b) orally, or in writing in any declaration or application, or in any document signed by him or on`
  line `his behalf, knowingly makes or connives at the making of any false statement or any omission; or`
  line
  line `(c) forges, alters, or tampers with any passport or any naval, military, air force, police, or official`
  line `pass, permit, certificate, licence, or other document of a similar character (hereinafter in this section`
  line `referred to as an official document) or knowingly uses or has. in his possession any such forged,`
  line `altered, or irregular official document; or`
  line
  line `(d) personates, or falsely represents himself to be, a person holding, or in the employment of a`
  line `person -holding, office under Government, or to be or not to be a person to whom an official`
  line `document or secret official code or pass word has been duly issued or communicated, or with intent to`
  line `obtain an official document, secret official code or pass word, whether for himself or any other`
  line `person, knowingly makes any false statement; or`
  line
  line `(e) uses, or has in his possession or under his control, without the authority of the department of`
  line `the Government or the authority concerned, any die, seal or stamp of or belonging to, or used, made`
  line `or provided by, any department of the Government, or by any diplomatic, naval, military, or air force`
  line `authority appointed by or acting under the authority of Government, or any die, seal or stamp so`
  line `nearly resembling any such die, seal or stamp as to be calculated to deceive, or counterfeits any such`
  line `die, seal or stamp, or knowingly uses, or has in his possession or under his control, any such`
  line `counterfeited die, seal or stamp;`
  line
  line `he shall be guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person for any purpose prejudicial to the safety of the State`
  line
  line `(a) retains any official document, whether or not completed or issued for use, when he has no`
  line `right to retain it, or when it is contrary to his duty to retain it, or wilfully fails to comply with any`
  line `directions issued by any department of the Government or any person authorised by such department`
  line `with regard to the return or disposal thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) allows any other person to have possession of any official document issued for his use alone,`
  line `or communicates any secret official code or pass word so issued, or, without lawful authority or`
  line `excuse, has in his possession any official document or secret official code or pass word issued for the`
  line `use of some person other than himself, or, on obtaining possession of any official document by`
  line `findink or otherwise, wilfully fails to restore it to the person or authority by whom or for whose use it`
  line `was issued, or to a police officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) without lawful authority or excuse, manufactures or sells, or has in his possession for sale, any`
  line `such die, seal or stamp as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `he shall be guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) A person guilty of an offence under this section shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to ^2[three years], or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-section (2) of section 3 shall apply, for the purpose of proving a purpose`
  line `prejudicial to the safety of the State, to any prosecution for an offence under this section relating to the`
  line `naval, military or air force affairs of Government, or to any secret official code in like manner as they`
  line `apply, for the purpose of proving a purpose prejudicial to the safety or interests of the State, to`
  line `prosecutions for offences punishable under that section ^3***.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 6, for "two years".`
  line
  line `2. The words "with imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years" omitted by s. 6, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37115)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Interfering with officers of the police or members of the Armed Forces of the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37115&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person in the vicinity of any prohibited place shall obstruct, knowingly mislead or`
  line `otherwise interfere with or impede, any police officer, or any member of ^1`
  line `[the Armed Forces of the`
  line `Union] engaged on guard, Sentry, patrol, or other similar duty in relation to the prohibited place.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person acts in contravention of the provisions of this section, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to ^2`
  line `[three years], or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "His Majesty's Forces".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 7, for "two years".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (37116)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duty of giving information as to commission of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37116&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every`
  line `person to give on demand to a Superintendent of Police, or other police officer not below the rank of`
  line `Inspector, empowered by an Inspector-General or Commissioner of Police in this behalf, or to any`
  line `member of ^1`
  line `[the Armed Forces of the Union] engaged on guard, sentry, patrol or other similar duty, any`
  line `information in his power relating to an offence or suspected offence under section 3 or under section 3`
  line `read with section 9 and, if so required, and upon tender of his reasonable expenses, to attend at such`
  line `reasonable time and place as may be specified for the purpose of furnishing such information.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person fails to give any such information or to attend as aforesaid, he shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment which may extend to ^2`
  line `[three years], or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "His Majesty's Forces".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 8, for "two years".`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (37117)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Attempts, incitements, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37117&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Any person who attempts to commit or abets the commission of an`
  line `offence under this Act shall be punishable with the same punishment, and be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against in the same manner as if he had committed such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (37118)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Penalty for harbouring spies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 9, for "one year".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37118&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person knowingly harbours any person whom he`
  line `knows or has reasonable grounds for supposing to be a person who is about to commit or who has`
  line `committed an offence under section 3 or under section 3 read with section 9 or knowingly permits to meet`
  line `or assemble in any premises in his occupation or under his control any such persons, he shall be guilty of`
  line `an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every person having harboured any such person as aforesaid, or`
  line `permitted to meet or assemble in any premises in his occupation or under his control`
  line `any such persons as aforesaid, to give on demand to a Superintendent of Police or other police officer not below the rank of Inspector empowered by an Inspector-General or Commissioner of Police`
  line `in this behalf, any information in his power relating to any such person or persons, and if any`
  line `person fails to give any such information, he shall be guilty of an offence under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) A person guilty of an offence under this section shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to ^1`
  line `[three years], or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (37119)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Search-warrants.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37119&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a Presidency Magistrate, Magistrate of the first class of Subdivisional Magistrate is satisfied by information on oath that there is reasonable ground for`
  line `suspecting that an offence under this Act has been or is about to be committed, he may grant a`
  line `search-warrant authorising any police officer named therein, not being below the rank of an`
  line `officer in charge of a police station, to enter at any time any premises or place named in the`
  line `warrant, if necessary, by force, and to search the premises or place and every person found`
  line `therein, and to seize any sketch, plan, model, article, note or document, or anything of a like`
  line `nature, or anything which is evidence of an offence under this Act having been or being about to`
  line `be committed which he may find on the premises or place or any such person, and with regard`
  line `to or in connection with which he has reasonable ground for suspecting that an offence under`
  line `this Act has been or is about to be committed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where it appears to a police officer, not being below the rank of Superintendent, that the`
  line `case is one of great emergency, and that in the interests of the State immediate action is`
  line `necessary, he may by a written order under his hand give to any police officer the like authority`
  line `as- may be given by the warrant of a Magistrate under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Where action has been taken by a police officer under sub-section (2) he shall, as soon as may be,`
  line `report such action, in a Presidency-town to the Chief Presidency Magistrate, and outside such town to the`
  line `District or Sub-divisional Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (37120)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provisions of section 337 of Act 5 of 1898 to apply to offences under sections 3, 5 and 7.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37120&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Provisions of section 337 of Act 5 of 1898 to apply to offences under sections 3, 5 and 7.—The provisions of section 337 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898^2`
  line `shall apply in relation to an`
  line `offence punishable under section 3 or under section 5 or under section 7 or under any of the`
  line `said sections 3, 5 and 7 read with section 9, as they apply in relation to an offence punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 12.`
  line
  line `2. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), s. 306.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (37121)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Restriction of trial of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37121&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court (other than that of a Magistrate of the`
  line `first class specially empowered in this behalf by the ^1`
  line `[appropriate Government] which is`
  line `inferior to that of a District or Presidency Magistrate shall try any offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person under trial before a Magistrate for an offence under this Act at any time`
  line `before a charge is framed claims to be tried by the Court of Session, the Magistrate shall, if he`
  line `does not discharge the accused, commit the case for trial by that Court, notwithstan ding that it is`
  line `not a case exclusively triable by that Court.`
  line
  line `(3) No Court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act unless upon complaint made`
  line `by order of, or under authority from, the ^2`
  line `[appropriate Government] ^3`
  line `*** or some officer`
  line `empowered by the ^4`
  line `[appropriate Government] in this behalf.`
  line
  line ^5
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of the trial of a person for an offence under this Act, the offence`
  line `may be deemed to have been committed either at the place in which the same actually wa s`
  line `committed or at any place in ^6`
  line `[India] in which the offender may be found.`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(5) In this section, the "appropriate Government" means—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to any offences under section 5 not connected with a prohibited place or with a`
  line `foreign power, the State Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to any other offence, the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. ibid., for "Governor-General in Council".`
  line
  line `3. The words "the Local Government" omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. The proviso omitted by Act 24 of 1967, s. 11.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (37122)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Exclusion of public from proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37122&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `In addition and without prejudice to any`
  line `powers which a Court may possess to order the exclusion of the public from any proceedings if,`
  line `in the course of proceedings before a Court against any person for an offence under this Act or`
  line `the proceedings on appeal, or in the course of the trial of a person under this Act, application is`
  line `made by the prosecution, on the ground that the publication of any evidenc e to be given or of`
  line `any statement to be made in the course of the proceedings would be prejudicial to the safety of`
  line `the State, that all or any portion of the public shall be excluded during any part of the hearing,`
  line `the Court may make an order to that effect, but the passing of sentence shall in any case take`
  line `place in public.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (37123)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1967, s. 12, for section 15.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011&sectionId=37123&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00042_192319_1523344792011
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Offences by companies.-- (1) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of business of the company, as well as the company,`
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to`
  line `such punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his`
  line `knowledge or that he exercied all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act`
  line `has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any negligence on the part of, any director,`
  line `manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this section,`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individual; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (37124)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Repealed..
  content `[Repeals.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1927 (12 of 1927), s. 2 and Sch.`
